                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Sp1/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-31T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 1, 11.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>714. German submarine <hi rend="italic">B–23</hi> entered Corunna July 29, 3 p.m.
                    British and Guatemalan Consuls telegraphed Captain General at Ferrol requesting
                    internment. He replied ordering submarine to Ferrol where it will be interned
                    until close of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
